"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045966","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-01-28","<p>Work on a revised approved document B was in hand, but was put on hold when the independent review of building regulations and fire safety was commissioned following the Grenfell Tower fire. A consultation draft of a clarified approved document was published for consultation in July 2018 and a further call for evidence for a full technical review was published in December.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2019-01-28T17:03:16.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045966/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045966/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045966/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-01-22","Lakanal House: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, for what reasons the full review of approved document B called for by the inquest into the Lakanal House fire was not carried out.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","211236"
