"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046061","Department for Education","false","2019-01-30","<p>Data on children looked-after in independent living without live-in support is not collected or published by the department. The department collects annual data on looked-after children in independent living, with or without live-in support.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-01-30T15:34:55.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046061/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046061/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046061/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-01-22","Supported Housing: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent estimate he has made of the number of (a) 16 and (b) 17 year olds living in unsupported independent living accommodation.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","211269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046062","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-01-28","<p>The public subsidy and most recent actual take-up figures can be found on our public-facing document - Link below:</p><p><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Hs00bNsyRV1WoOt-fow3rsNXzpcKg26AsOWvk1bvJRk/edit#gid=0" target="_blank">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Hs00bNsyRV1WoOt-fow3rsNXzpcKg26AsOWvk1bvJRk/edit#gid=0</a></p><p>Contract specific data is held by each Local Body for their own contracts, so you would need to direct this request to them. Please note that some of this data is commercially sensitive.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2019-01-28T17:53:55.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046062/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046062/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046062/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-01-22","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what the (a) the supplier contribution, (b) estimated take-up; (c) actual take-up, and (d) associated take-up clawback are for each project involved in the roll-out of rural broadband.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","211080"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046063","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-30","<p>​The Government's priority for all sessions of the UN Human Rights Council is to ensure that it holds those responsible for human rights violations and abuses to account, effectively addresses global threats to human rights, and strengthens protections for the future. At the 40th session, we envisage specific priorities will include the human rights situation in Syria, Sri Lanka, Burma, Iran, Democratic People's Republic of Korea, Libya and South Sudan, and thematic priorities of media freedom, human rights defenders, and freedom of religion or belief.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2019-01-30T11:41:58.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046063/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046063/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046063/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-22","UN Human Rights Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will list his Department's priorities for the United Nations Human Rights Council session in March 2019.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","211086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046064","Treasury","false","2019-01-28","<p>The Government published a consultation on a single policy proposal for the breathing space scheme in October 2018. The consultation proposed that as wide a range of an individual’s personal debts as possible would be included in the scheme, including certain tax and benefit debts.</p><p> </p><p>The consultation closes on 29 January and the Government intends to confirm its approach to these aspects of the scheme in its response.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2019-01-28T14:14:17.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046064/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046064/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046064/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-22","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department has plans to included the debts owed to (a) HMRC, and (b) other government bodies in the Breathing Space scheme.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","211178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046065","Department for Education","false","2019-01-28","<p>The department does not have information on whether the local authorities that commissioned forensic tests from Trimega, between January 2010 and April 2014, have carried out a case by case assessment of the effect of toxicology on decision-making in relation to the welfare of children. However, the department wrote to local authorities on 17 November 2017 and 16 February 2018, asking them to review whether they had commissioned forensic tests from Trimega Laboratories Limited between January 2010 to April 2014, and to consider whether there was a need to take further action in order to fulfil their safeguarding responsibilities.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","211273","2019-01-28T17:24:12.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046065/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046065/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046065/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-01-22","Forensic Science: Misconduct","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether any of the local authorities that commissioned forensic tests from Trimega Laboratories Limited between January 2010 and April 2014 have carried out a case-by-case assessment of the effect of toxicology on decision-making in relation to the welfare of children.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","211270"
