"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045651","Home Office","false","2019-01-29","<p>Information on visa and immigration income is published annually in The Home Office Annual Report and Accounts. Refer to links below for the last 3 years figures.</p><p>FY2017/18 – page 126:</p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/727179/6_4360_HO_Annual_report_WEB.PDF" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/727179/6_4360_HO_Annual_report_WEB.PDF</a></p><p>FY2016/17 - page 117:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/627853/ho_annual_report_and_accounts_2016_2017.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/627853/ho_annual_report_and_accounts_2016_2017.pdf</a></p><p>FY2015/16 - page 134:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/539638/HO_AR_16_gov.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/539638/HO_AR_16_gov.pdf</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-01-29T14:47:48.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045651/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045651/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045651/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-21","Visas: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what sums his Department received in payments for visa applications in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","210535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045652","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-29","<p>On 6 November 2018 I spoke with the German Ambassador to seek his assistance to make it easier for UK Thalidomide Survivors to apply for funding from the Contergan Foundation. He explained that only those who took the drug supplied by Grunenthal directly would be eligible for funding. The German Government do not consider that they have any liability for those who took the drug distributed under licence in the UK. Therefore, very few, if any, UK survivors would be eligible for this compensation.</p><p>I and UK officials have done all we can to address this issue with the German Government. We will continue to encourage constructive dialogue between the Thalidomide Trust and the German Government to explore what other support may be available.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-01-29T16:12:53.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045652/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045652/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045652/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-21","Germany: Thalidomide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 30 October 2018 to Question 185531 on Germany: Thalidomide, what progress he has made on making it easier for UK Thalidomide victims to apply for compensation from the Contergan Foundation.","false","Biography information for Janet Daby","Lewisham East","Janet Daby","210710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045653","Department for Transport","false","2019-01-24","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency is currently amending the Assessing Fitness to Drive guidance on the use of new monitoring technologies for people with diabetes. The revised guidance is due to be published in February. This will allow the testing of interstitial fluid for driving licensing purposes for people with diabetes who drive cars or motorcycles. Drivers of goods vehicles and buses must continue to monitor blood glucose levels.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-01-24T13:16:18.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045653/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045653/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045653/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-21","Driving: Diabetes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with the DVLA on testing blood glucose levels using flash and continuous glucose monitoring technology for the purposes of assessing fitness to drive; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","210480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045654","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-01-25","<p>We are currently preparing for a call for evidence to be issued in the spring.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2019-01-25T13:02:16.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045654/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045654/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045654/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-01-21","Ivory","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress he has made on the consultation to include additional ivory species in the Ivory Act 2018, and whether he has set a date for this consultation to be published.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","210623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045655","Department for Transport","false","2019-01-28","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring that disabled people have the same access to transport and opportunities to seek employment as everyone else. In July 2018 the Government launched the Inclusive Transport Strategy (ITS) which sets out key policy and investment priorities to deliver an inclusive transport system.</p><p><em> </em></p><p>Access to Work is a publicly funded employment support programme that aims to help more disabled people start, or stay in, work. It can provide practical and financial support for people who have a disability or long term physical or mental health condition. The scheme is demand-led and offers a discretionary grant, administered by Jobcentre Plus (JCP). Support for disabled workers can include travel to work and travel within work as well as specialised aids, equipment and support workers.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-01-28T15:52:59.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045655/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045655/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045655/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-21","Transport: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that disabled people have suitable transport access when seeking employment opportunities.","false","Biography information for Kirstene Hair","Angus","Kirstene Hair","210711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045656","Home Office","false","2019-01-28","<p>The roll-out of the Seasonal Workers Pilot remains on track and will be implemented in spring this year. A commencement date for the pilot will be announced in the coming weeks.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-01-28T12:17:58.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045656/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045656/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1045656/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-21","Agriculture: Seasonal Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what progress he has made on the roll-out of the pilot Seasonal Agricultural Workers Scheme.","false","Biography information for Kirstene Hair","Angus","Kirstene Hair","210712"
